                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Got our level 68 charm spell today, Compel. So far it seems that all L65-67 mobs charmed by this spell in OoW zones hit for 260. This is true for at least Walls of Slaughter, Dranik's instanced zone, the Hollows, Ruined City of Dranik. Those mobs charmed by Command of Druzzil (level 64 mobs i assume) in same zones always hit for 245.
<br />
Basically, there is even no point of using Compel, unless there are only 65+ mobs around, because a 15 damage increase simply aint worth it. I would like to remind you, that level 66-67 mobs usially hit very fast for past 700, also most seem to quad, and there is no WoM upgrade. I'm not even looking at our new 6 second stun, as with 2,0 casting time and 6,0 duration it is pretty much useless. Mobs that hit for 700+ after break will rape you in very short time, unless maybe snared. 
<br />
Very sad indeed, a 260 damage charmed by normally hitting for 731 mob is not even 30% of max. damage.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Changed topic's name a little to reflect issue being discussed: new 65+ charm spells in OoW</span></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Alena on Mon Sep 20, 2004 1:28 am; edited 2 times in total</span></td>
