                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm sure it'll be adjusted.
<br />

<br />
But don't look for it to be adjusted very much.
<br />

<br />
I'm sorry, but even speaking as an enchanter, I have to say that charm NEEDED to be changed.  When I can charm a pet and solo a named in BoT, there's something very, very wrong.  When my pet can out-dps an entire group, and it will never touch me on a charm break because a ranger snared it before it was charmed, something is very, very wrong.
<br />

<br />
Charm was always about risk vs. reward, but the balance of risk vs. reward has become skewed.  Ranger snare virtually eliminated risk by making the enchanter all but untouchable if the chanter had room to move around, but the reward did not change.  Focus effects significantly reduces risk to the soloing charmer, while reward remained the same.  They have to rediscover that delicate balance between making charm worth using and keeping it from becoming overpowering.
<br />

<br />
No, in its current form, I don't think charm is really fair, because it swings too heavily to the "risk" side, where before it was too heavily on the "reward" side.  But, IMO, I'd much rather them look into much more pressing issues with enchanters, like the lack of am upgrade to WoM, or an AE stun that doesn't suck, or returning us to our prior role of CC instead of our current roles of the keeper of the charmed pet or buffbot.
<br />

<br />
They can come back to charming after they look into those things.  IN MY OPINION.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Mistress Auli, Dark Elf Coercer of Vazaelle
<br />
Elder Binter, Vah Shir Prophet of Vazaelle</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
