                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Mez bounces off WoS mobs with some regularity.
<br />

<br />
Why in the world would I be insane enough to use charm for crowd control?  It would last a fraction of a second.
<br />

<br />
Charm wasn't redesigned for CC.  If it was redesinged for CC, it would have a massive resist adjust on it.  They redesigned it to be balanded DPS against other classes, and utterly discounted any extra risk from charm breaks.
<br />

<br />
And the only word we've heard form SOE is "it isn't a nerf, it is a content change" indirectly.  Can we at least get some dialog?
<br />

<br />
Over half of the enchanters <span style="font-weight: bold">agree charm DPS needs lowering</span>, yet SOE hasn't even swung by to give us a heads up.  And sorry nany, second hand relayed half detailed information doesn't cut it -- playing telephone with the developers will result in things like "the changes affect the new charms" and "DPS is 1/2 while charmed", neither of which are true, but where your impression originally.
<br />

<br />
Go look at how the devs chatted with the bards on the PBAOE kiting nerf.
<br />

<br />
I <span style="font-weight: bold">support</span> dropping charm DPS.  Hell, I posted an idea which was worse (I aslo halved charm pet tankability), but I never in my wildest dreams thought anyone would be so silly as to make a pet do  half damage to mobs and full damage on charm breaks.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">edit</span>  Auli, I'm sorry you don't consider charm to be important.  Maybe you are one of the many enchanters who didn't charm much, who doesn't view keeping a charmed pet around to be as natural as breathing.   I use the pet for crowd control, DPS, and pulling.  There are enchanters in my guild who are frightened by charming, or who don't like it, because it takes too much effort.  So be it.  However, other people really like having a charmed pet around.
<br />

<br />
I support stronger animations and DC pets for those enchanters who are risk-averse.  But, having an ex-pet attack for triple damage compared to charmed damage is just ridiculous.  They are obvoiusly ok with near-zero risk charming: bards have charm, and they can outrun the pets, snare/mez them on the run, and recharm in barely more time as it takes our spell gems to refresh.  So why is it too much to ask that we be able to take a low-DPS unhasted pet and recharm it without building a group around the task?</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
