So you have too many mezzed and charmed mobs in camp.
<br />

<br />
Each of these mobs is costing you 25-30 mana/tick, with low mana cost variance and high reliability.
<br />

<br />
Charm costs 14-odd mana/tick on low MR mobs, but has a high variance and is frontloaded cost-wise, and has low reliability.
<br />

<br />
You are taking a theoretically dangerous situation (too many mezzed mobs), and saving half a mob's worth of CC mana (on average) in exchange for a large increase in risk (charm breaks at a bad time, interfears with mezzing on the other mobs, and you start wiping).
<br />

