                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>fyrestormm wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">One question do you play an enchanter?  If you are in the rare situation where you are holding down a large number of hard hitting mobs, you do not go and charm one of them.  As it is you are to busy tashing and slowing and keeping all the mobs mez, to have any extra time  to watch a charmed pet.  The last thing you want to do is take a situation where everything is undercontrol and add some risk by charming a mob that puts out substandard DPS.  Now if you are in a gimp zone where the enchanter can tank 2 of the slowed mobs easy, then go ahead and have some fun and charm one of the mobs.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
When I group in BoT I'll use charm for cc if we get trained at fourways. Mez everything, tash one land charm, tash others remezz (group have one to play with at this time) send pet in. Stay away from pet, etc,etc. We've cleared through great trains like this. Used the same thing on a nasty tactics pull this weekend, eventually kept the petted mob for a bit of extra dps as we cleared down to the forge area. Tipt/vxed I've always got a pet anyway so its a moot point, beyond the trials I'm informed you don't really have the option. Not elementally flagged yet, so can't really comment about that, although I hear alot are flagged mez/charm immune. 
<br />

<br />
